---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { url } from '../utils/url';

const lastUpdated = 'March 11, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Merrily Plan privacy policy. Learn how we collect, use, and protect your data when using our wedding planning app."
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50 via-white to-accent-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="section-heading mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-12 md:py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-gray max-w-none">
      <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Welcome to Merrily Plan ("we," "our," or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy
        and ensuring you understand how your data is handled when you use our wedding planning
        application and marketing website at <strong>merrilyplan.com</strong> (the "Site") and
        <strong>app.merrilyplan.com</strong> (the "App").
      </p>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, your rights
        regarding your data, and how to contact us with questions.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

      <h3>2.1 Free Plan (No Account Required)</h3>
      <p>
        The Free plan operates entirely within your browser using local storage. We do <strong>not</strong>
        collect, transmit, or store any of your wedding planning data on our servers when you use the
        Free plan. Your data stays on your device.
      </p>

      <h3>2.2 Pro Plan (Account Required)</h3>
      <p>When you create a Pro account, we may collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account information</strong>: email address, name, and password (hashed)</li>
        <li><strong>Wedding planning data</strong>: the information you enter into the app, including
          budgets, guest lists, vendor details, and other planning content, synced to our cloud servers</li>
        <li><strong>Payment information</strong>: processed securely by our payment processor (Stripe).
          We do not store your full credit card number.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage data</strong>: features used, session duration, and device information for
          improving the product</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2.3 Marketing Website</h3>
      <p>When you visit merrilyplan.com, we may collect:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cookie data</strong>: subject to your consent preferences (see Section 6)</li>
        <li><strong>Contact form submissions</strong>: name, email, and message content when you contact us</li>
        <li><strong>Newsletter signups</strong>: email address if you subscribe to our blog updates</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics data</strong>: anonymized page views, referral sources, and browser type
          (only with your consent)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use collected information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide and maintain the Merrily Plan service</li>
        <li>Sync your wedding planning data across devices (Pro plan)</li>
        <li>Process payments and manage subscriptions</li>
        <li>Respond to your inquiries and support requests</li>
        <li>Send important service updates and announcements</li>
        <li>Improve our app and website based on usage patterns</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We will <strong>never</strong> sell your personal information to third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We only share your data with third parties in these limited circumstances:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Service providers</strong>: hosting (cloud infrastructure), payment processing
          (Stripe), and email delivery services that help us operate the platform</li>
        <li><strong>Legal requirements</strong>: when required by law, subpoena, or government request</li>
        <li><strong>Collaboration partners</strong>: when you explicitly share your wedding plan with
          another user (Pro plan feature)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement industry-standard security measures including encryption in transit (HTTPS/TLS),
        encrypted storage, secure authentication, and regular security reviews. However, no method of
        transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Our marketing website uses cookies categorized as follows:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Strictly Necessary</strong>: essential for the website to function (always active)</li>
        <li><strong>Functional</strong>: remember your preferences and settings</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics</strong>: help us understand how visitors use the site</li>
        <li><strong>Marketing</strong>: used to personalize ads and measure campaign performance</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can manage your cookie preferences at any time using the cookie settings button on our
        website. Non-essential cookies are only activated after you provide explicit consent.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights:</p>

      <h3>7.1 General Rights</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong>: request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Correction</strong>: request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li><strong>Deletion</strong>: request deletion of your personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Portability</strong>: export your data in a machine-readable format (JSON export
          is available in both Free and Pro plans)</li>
        <li><strong>Objection</strong>: object to processing of your data for specific purposes</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>7.2 GDPR (European Economic Area)</h3>
      <p>
        If you are in the EEA, you have additional rights under the General Data Protection Regulation,
        including the right to lodge a complaint with your local supervisory authority. Our lawful bases
        for processing are: consent, contract performance, and legitimate interests.
      </p>

      <h3>7.3 CCPA (California)</h3>
      <p>
        California residents have the right to know what personal information is collected, request
        deletion, and opt out of the sale of personal information. We do <strong>not</strong> sell
        personal information. To exercise your rights, contact us at the address below.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain your personal data only as long as necessary to provide our services and fulfill the
        purposes described in this policy. When you delete your account, we remove your personal data
        within 30 days, except where retention is required by law.
      </p>
      <p>
        Free plan data is stored only on your device and is never transmitted to our servers. You can
        clear it at any time by clearing your browser data.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Merrily Plan is not intended for use by children under the age of 16. We do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children. If we learn that we have collected data from a
        child under 16, we will delete it promptly.
      </p>

      <h2>10. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Your data may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. We ensure
        appropriate safeguards are in place, including Standard Contractual Clauses where applicable,
        to protect your data during international transfers.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes
        by posting the updated policy on this page with a new "Last updated" date. Your continued use
        of our services after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or want to exercise your data rights, please
        contact us:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email</strong>: <a href="mailto:hello@merrilyplan.com">hello@merrilyplan.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Contact form</strong>: <a href={url('/contact')}>merrilyplan.com/contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
